    {
      "id": "view-authoring-intro",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "View Authoring Checklist",
      "position": {
        "x": -700,
        "y": -700
      },
      "width": 860,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# View Authoring Golden Path\n\nThis graph is a *separate* test from bridges/declarations.\n\nGoal: prove that a human can:\n\n1. create a view node\n2. edit intent/payload + render-shape\n3. enter renderable content (markdown/html/svg/text)\n4. assign that view in the declaration\n\nThis does not attempt to prove \"a class uses the view\" yet. It proves the authoring substrate is real and consistent."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-steps",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Steps",
      "position": {
        "x": 200,
        "y": -700
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Manual Steps (quick)\n\n1. Add a `view` node.\n2. Edit it: set `intent=node`, `payload=node.web.detail`.\n3. Set render-shape kind to `markdown` and enter markdown content.\n4. Confirm only the active render field is visible (not 5 competing fields).\n5. In the declaration editor, set **Primary Node View** to that view node.\n6. Repeat for an editor view: `intent=editor`, `payload=editor.web`.\n\nIf any step fails, capture what you saw and what you expected."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-01",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 1",
      "position": {
        "x": -700,
        "y": -340
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 200,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 1: Create A View Node\n\nAction:\n- Create a new node of type `view`.\n\nPass condition:\n- A view node appears on canvas.\n- It has an Edit button.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-02",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 2",
      "position": {
        "x": -110,
        "y": -340
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 200,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 2: Edit Intent + Payload\n\nAction:\n- Open the view node editor.\n- Set:\n  - intent: `node`\n  - payload: `node.web.detail`\n\nPass condition:\n- The view node header/chip reflects the new payload.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-03",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 3",
      "position": {
        "x": 480,
        "y": -340
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 3: Choose Render Kind + Enter Content\n\nAction:\n- Set render-shape kind to `markdown`.\n- Enter markdown content (include a header and a list).\n\nPass condition:\n- Content persists after closing editor.\n- Preview reflects the new payload content.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-04",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 4",
      "position": {
        "x": -700,
        "y": -70
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 4: Field Hygiene (Primary Format)\n\nAction:\n- Switch render kind between `markdown` and `html`.\n\nPass condition:\n- Only the active render field is visible.\n- Switching kind does not silently destroy other content.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-05",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 5",
      "position": {
        "x": -110,
        "y": -70
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 5: Assign In Declaration\n\nAction:\n- Open declaration editor.\n- Set **Primary Node View** to your authored view node.\n\nPass condition:\n- Your view node appears in the selector list.\n- Selection persists.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-step-06",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Step 6",
      "position": {
        "x": 480,
        "y": -70
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Step 6: Author An Editor View\n\nAction:\n- Create another `view` node.\n- Set:\n  - intent: `editor`\n  - payload: `editor.web`\n\nPass condition:\n- It appears in the declaration editor selector for **Primary Editor View**.\n\nResult:\n- [ ] PASS\n- [ ] FAIL\n\nNotes:"
      }
    },
    {
