      }
    },
    {
      "id": "view-authoring-notes",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Notes",
      "position": {
        "x": 80,
        "y": 260
      },
      "width": 720,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Notes / Diagnostics\n\nIf the view editor looks like an \"error editor\":\n- capture the view node type (`view`, `node-view`, etc.)\n- capture which editor surface opened (header shows `View: ...`)\n- capture whether the edit button exists on the view node\n\nThis graph is intentionally simple: it is about authoring and assignment, not consumption."
      }
    }
  ],
